title: How Concessions Are Making a Modest But Notable Comeback in 2022
description: Two years after former President Donald J. Trump rejected the results of the election, many of his supporters embraced the rituals of losing amicably.
dc:creator: Glenn Thrush
media:credit: Hilary Swift for The New York Times
media:description: Mehmet Oz, the Republican Senate candidate who was defeated by Lt. Gov. John Fetterman in Pennsylvania, speaks at the Newtown Athletic Club on Tuesday.
